The paper deals with object detection from images captured by UAVs, which is a computer vision problem (cs.CV). The authors propose a deep learning approach to disentangle nuisances specific to UAV images, which involves training a model to be robust to varying flying altitudes, adverse weather conditions, dynamically changing viewing angles, etc. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the robotics sub-category (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves adversarial training, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of meta-data, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with object detection, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM).
